## Development Build __VERSION__

Unstable dev build for [slskdN](https://github.com/snapetech/slskdn), an unofficial fork of [slskd](https://github.com/slskd/slskd). This channel exists so new product work ships early, especially SongID and Discovery Graph changes that need real-world use before they belong in stable.

### Focus Areas In This Channel
- **SongID**: direct identification from URLs, text, and local media with evidence fusion, durable queueing, mix decomposition, ranked track/album/discography actions, and live run progress.
- **Discovery Graph / Constellation**: atlas-mode graph browsing across SongID, MusicBrainz, and search with queue-nearby, compare, recenter, and saved-branch workflows.
- **Acquisition experiments**: identity-first download planning, top-candidate fan-out, split-track planning, and other first-class acquisition changes before they graduate to stable.
- **Fork platform work**: packaging, mesh, Solid, and other network/runtime changes may appear here first.

### Install
```bash
# Arch Linux
yay -S slskdn-dev

# Fedora / RHEL
sudo dnf copr enable slskdn/slskdn-dev
sudo dnf install slskdn-dev

# Ubuntu / Debian
sudo add-apt-repository ppa:keefshape/slskdn
sudo apt update
sudo apt install slskdn-dev

# Docker
docker pull ghcr.io/snapetech/slskdn:dev-latest

# macOS
brew install snapetech/slskdn/slskdn-dev
```

Direct download works too: extract the archive for your platform and run `slskd`.

